</code></pre> <p>Code Property Graphs (CPGs) are a representation of program code that combines different code representations into a single graph. This unified representation includes abstract syntax trees (ASTs), control flow graphs (CFGs), control dependence graphs (CDGs), and data dependence graphs (DDGs). CPGs enable comprehensive analysis, which makes them a powerful tool for detecting vulnerabilities and understanding code structure. For further details, refer to this thesis.</p>

